{
  "texts": [
    "TMZ induced robust PCNA ubiquitination in MMR+ cells but not in isogenic cells lacking MLH1 or MSH2 (Fig. 3e, g).",
    "Therefore, MMRmediated processing of TMZ-induced lesions is required for RAD18 pathway activation.",
    "In MGMT-expressing LN18 cells which do not accumulate O 6 mG, RAD18-ablation did not lead to persistent DDR signaling after TMZ treatment (Fig. 3h).",
    "It is known that following mispair recognition, the nuclease EXO1 excises the daughter strand to expose ssDNA.",
    "Ablating EXO1 (using siRNA) led to attenuation of PCNA mono-ubiquitination (Fig. 3i)."
  ]
}